verses.text:
The 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* \w reigneth|strong="H4427"\w*, he is \w clothed|strong="H3847"\w* with \w majesty|strong="H1348"\w*; the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* is \w clothed|strong="H3847"\w* with \w strength|strong="H5797"\w*, \add wherewith\add* he hath \w girded|strong="H0247"\w* himself: the \w world|strong="H8398"\w* also is \w stablished|strong="H3559"\w*, that it cannot be \w moved|strong="H4131"\w*.

Thy \w throne|strong="H3678"\w* \add is\add* \w established|strong="H3559"\w* of \w old|strong="H0227"\w*: thou \add art\add* from \w everlasting|strong="H5769"\w*.\f + \fr 93.2 \ft of old: Heb. from then\f*

The \w floods|strong="H5104"\w* have lifted \w up|strong="H5375"\w*, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, the \w floods|strong="H5104"\w* have lifted \w up|strong="H5375"\w* their \w voice|strong="H6963"\w*; the \w floods|strong="H5104"\w* lift \w up|strong="H5375"\w* their \w waves|strong="H1796"\w*.

The \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* on \w high|strong="H4791"\w* \add is\add* \w mightier|strong="H0117"\w* than the \w noise|strong="H6963"\w* of \w many|strong="H7227"\w* \w waters|strong="H4325"\w*, \add yea, than\add* the \w mighty|strong="H0117"\w* \w waves|strong="H4867"\w* of the \w sea|strong="H3220"\w*.

Thy \w testimonies|strong="H5713"\w* are \w very|strong="H3966"\w* \w sure|strong="H0539"\w*: \w holiness|strong="H6944"\w* \w becometh|strong="H4998"\w* thine \w house|strong="H1004"\w*, O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, for \w ever|strong="H0753"\w*.\f + \fr 93.5 \ft for ever: Heb. to length of days\f*
